{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Stone"], "type": "title", "extent": [61, 71], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [71, 127], "text": ["Simulates a rough, non-descript stone material."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [127, 190], "text": ["This operator simulates a rough, non-descript stone material."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [190, 689], "text": ["The stone displacement consists of noisy bumps and cavities, whose\nrandomness is controlled by Bump Frequency (", {"text": ["bfreq"], "type": "code"}, "), Bump Amplitude\n(", {"text": ["bamp"], "type": "code"}, ") and Bump Roughness (", {"text": ["brough"], "type": "code"}, "). The amount of cavity chipping is\ndetermined by the Chip Amount (", {"text": ["chip"], "type": "code"}, ") input. By increasing the ", {"text": ["chip"], "type": "code"}, "\namount, you can make the stone look more porous. Additional displacement\ncan be passed in through the Bump Amount (", {"text": ["bump"], "type": "code"}, ") input. For an example of\nhow ", {"text": ["bump"], "type": "code"}, " is used, see the ", {"text": ["Stone Wall"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/stonewall", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/stonewall"}, " operator."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [689, 1020], "text": ["The \"Pepper\" inputs refer to the additional color noise that is\n\"peppered\" over the stone surface to make it look more realistic. The\nlook of the pepper noise is controlled by three inputs: Pepper Amplitude\n(", {"text": ["pamp"], "type": "code"}, "), Pepper Roughness (", {"text": ["prough"], "type": "code"}, "), and Bump Frequency (", {"text": ["bfreq"], "type": "code"}, "). The\nPepper Color (", {"text": ["peppercolor"], "type": "code"}, ") specifies its color."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1020, 1552], "text": ["If the Position (", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, ") input and the Normal (", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, ") input are not connected,\nthe global variables by the same names will be used instead. Typically\nyou will use ", {"text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, " as inputs for ", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, ", and\nwill not touch ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, " unless you want to apply additional displacement to\nthe stone surface using an operator such as ", {"text": ["Bump Noise"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise"}, ". If you need to\naccess the global variables directly, they are available from the ", {"text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1561, 1587], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/concrete", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/concrete"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1587, 1611], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/marble", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/marble"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1611, 1636], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1636, 1663], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/stonewall", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/stonewall"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1663, 1688], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/stucco", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/stucco"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1552, 1561], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Simulates a rough, non-descript stone material."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "namespace": null, "internal": "stone", "context": "vop", "type": "node", "icon": "VOP/stone"}, "title": ["Stone"]}